BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Spring Plant Sale to Benefit our Native Plant Nursery
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260502T090000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260502T140000
UID:06c7e4c25db9d9600de3f00ba8f5c94c@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:We are thrilled to announce our fifth annual Spring Plant Sale
 ! We are offering over 40 species of plants that were homegrown in our Nat
 ive Plant Nursery from seed to plant plug. Many species are grown from loc
 ally collected seed at nearby preserves. All species are ethically sourced
  and native to southern Indiana\, providing benefits to local pollinators 
 and wildlife. Plants sell for $4 each\, with all proceeds going back into 
 nursery operations and native plant restoration projects. Stop by to learn
  from experienced staff and volunteers on the advantages of gardening with
  native species!
LOCATION:Bloomingfoods East Parking Lot
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/03/spring-plant-sale-to-benefit-our
 -native-plant-nursery/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Preserve-a-Preserve: Weed Wrangle at Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Pr
 eserve
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260424T100000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260424T120000
UID:ef90a29be22ef407407b7d80f15a02dd@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Spend a day tromping through wetlands during our Beanblossom B
 ottoms Nature Preserve Weed Wrangle as we work together to remove invasive
  cattails. Over the past couple of years\, storms and tornado damage have 
 opened the canopy in parts of the preserve\, allowing more sunlight to rea
 ch the wetlands\, which causes aggressive species like cattails to spread.
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/03/preserve-a-preserve-weed-wrangle
 -at-beanblossom-bottoms-nature-preserve-2/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Fire on the Landscape with Sam Shoaf
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260404T090000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260404T120000
UID:35142d811bd1c1f3a93d2669a5a40101@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:The whippoorwill\, a species of concern here in Indiana\, has 
 found safe refuge in the recently burned areas of Downey Hill\, but why? J
 oin us for a guided hike through the Laura Hare Nature Preserve at Downey 
 Hill with Sam Shoaf\, Director of Operations and Burn Boss at Eco Logic\, 
 LLC\, to explore the vital role of fire in Indiana’s ecosystems. Sam wil
 l share insights into how prescribed burns are planned and conducted\, and
  how fire helps maintain healthy forests\, promote native plant growth\, a
 nd support wildlife diversity. Participants will walk through areas recent
 ly shaped by fire and learn how this natural process contributes to long-t
 erm habitat restoration and resilience.
LOCATION:The Laura Hare Nature Preserve at Downey Hill
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/03/fire-on-the-landscape-with-sam-s
 hoaf/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:WINGS: Map and Compass
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T090000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260329T120000
UID:51e3225e15f602217e2ce3106356e8aa@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Build your outdoor navigation skills at Porter West Preserve w
 ith our Women in Nature Gaining Skills Map and Compass Workshop. During th
 is event\, you&#8217\;ll learn the basics of land navigation\, including r
 eading topographic maps\, understanding compass bearings\, orienting yours
 elf in the field\, and planning routes across varied terrain. After learni
 ng the basics\, you’ll put your skills into practice on a challenge cour
 se across the preserve\, honing your ability to navigate confidently and a
 ccurately. This hike is a part of Women in Nature Gaining Skills\; to lear
 n more about this organization and its partnership with Sycamore Land Trus
 t\, visit WINGS on Facebook
LOCATION:Porter West Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/02/wings-map-and-compass/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:The Hidden World of Lichens with Gillian Harris
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T090000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260327T113000
UID:b4a8d332e6e97867d84898dd38a88ecb@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Discover the Hidden World of Lichens\, led by naturalist and a
 rtist Gillian Harris! Lichens\, which are a unique partnership between fun
 gi and algae or cyanobacteria\, are more than just “mossy stuff” on tr
 ees and rocks\; they’re fascinating indicators of air quality\, habitat 
 diversity\, and ecosystem health. As we hike\, we’ll observe these often
 -overlooked organisms in their many forms and learn about their biology\, 
 where they live\, and why they matter.
LOCATION:The Laura Hare Nature Preserve at Downey Hill
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/02/the-hidden-world-of-lichens-with
 -gillian-harris/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Preserve-a-Preserve: Weed Wrangle at Porter West
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T100000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260320T120000
UID:7a0f2fe9558579bf51532a13e94f9957@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join us at Porter West Preserve for a Preserve-a-Preserve Weed
  Wrangle where we will focus on cut-stumping invasive woody plants like Bu
 sh Honeysuckle\, Burning Bush and Autumn Olive. Volunteers will learn how 
 these invaders threaten ecosystem biodiversity and gain practical skills i
 n managing them safely and effectively. It’s a rewarding way to get outs
 ide\, make a real impact\, and help keep Porter West thriving for years to
  come!
LOCATION:Porter West Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/02/preserve-a-preserve-weed-wrangle
 -at-porter-west-2/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Monthly Birding: Wetlands and Waterfowl
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T080000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260314T103000
UID:b7d48be83e8a65a737d9661b280114be@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Spend a morning at our Carl Ziegler Wetlands with expert birde
 r Gary Langell for a waterfowl birding event! We’ll use binoculars and s
 potting scopes to observe ducks\, geese\, and other wetland species as the
 y move through this vibrant habitat. In March of 2025\, local eBird report
 s at the &#8220\;Dolan Wetlands&#8221\; included a diverse array of waterf
 owl\, including Northern Shovelers\, Gadwall\, Green‑winged Teal\, Ameri
 can Wigeon\, Hooded Mergansers\, and more! Come with your questions and cu
 riosity\; Gary is amazing at pointing out key traits for species identific
 ation! Carl Ziegler Wetlands is not open to the public.
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/02/monthly-birding-wetlands-and-wat
 erfowl/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Little Hikers: Eager Beavers
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T093000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260310T113000
UID:3bdf7f43d606a95239bb1ec03d3cee8a@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Beavers are the ecosystem engineers of nature! Join us for an 
 outdoor adventure as we explore how beavers build their dams\, shape the l
 andscape\, and create habitat for countless other species. Together we’l
 l take a short walk to observe an active beaver dam\, look for signs of be
 aver activity\, and discover what makes these busy animals so important to
  wetland ecosystems. At the end of our hike\, your Little Hikers will put 
 their knowledge to the test by building a beaver dam together!
LOCATION:Beanblossom Bottoms Nature Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/02/little-hikers-eager-beavers/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hike the Trust: Laura Hare Nature Preserve at Downey Hill
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T090000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260308T113000
UID:b906182b39df55d55c8c73f192ae2d03@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Experience the Laura Hare Nature Preserve at Downey Hill on a 
 guided hike as part of our Hike the Trust series! As winter gives way to e
 arly signs of spring\, we’ll explore the preserve’s woodlands and upla
 nd trails\, focusing on tree identification\, seasonal ecology\, and the s
 ubtle shifts in the landscape that signal the coming growing season. This 
 hike is a chance to compare habitats across ecoregions and enjoy the quiet
  beauty of southern Indiana’s forests in early spring.
LOCATION:The Laura Hare Nature Preserve at Downey Hill
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/02/hike-the-trust-laura-hare-nature
 -preserve-at-downey-hill/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Search for Skunk Cabbage at Powell Preserve
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T090000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T103000
UID:cb12dcc44b48561a2c29edc93b36eefa@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Not far from the parking lot at Powell Preserve and hidden by 
 the willows is a small patch of skunk cabbage\, one of Monroe County’s m
 ost fascinating wetland plants. With fewer than 30 documented occurrences 
 of skunk cabbage in the county\, this is a rare chance to observe it in bl
 oom. We&#8217\;ll discuss its remarkable thermogenic properties\, which al
 low the plant to generate heat and even melt surrounding snow to emerge ea
 rly in the season. While we&#8217\;re there\, we&#8217\;ll observe the str
 eam restoration\, seeing firsthand how restoration supports wetlands\, wat
 er quality\, and wildlife habitat. Powell Preserve is not currently open t
 o the public.
LOCATION:Powell Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2026/02/search-for-skunk-cabbage-at-powe
 ll-preserve/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
