BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Seed Collection at the Sam Shine Foundation Preserve
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260827T130000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260827T150000
UID:9ef8bc94b6d971f02721da6fbecea3f1@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join Education Director Saige Sentell and Bill Daniels\, volun
 teer co-manager of our Native Plant Nursery\, for a special volunteer oppo
 rtunity to learn how to ethically harvest and clean seeds for habitat rest
 oration projects\, targeting native prairie species such as prairie conefl
 ower\, rattlesnake master\, swamp milkweed\, false blue indigo\, and more.
  The seeds you collect will be used in educational programming throughout 
 our 26-county service area and in future restoration projects at our prese
 rves. Participants will be working off-trail in tall vegetation. Long slee
 ves\, long pants\, sturdy shoes\, and sun protection are required. The Sam
  Shine Foundation Preserve is not open to the public. Registration is requ
 ired.
LOCATION:Sam Shine Foundation Preserve
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2025/08/seed-collection-at-the-sam-shine
 -foundation-preserve/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Group Hike: Laura Hare Nature Preserve at Downey Hill
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260823T090000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260823T120000
UID:dd639bb35143caf7ed71b5cc62b43852@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Join Saige Sentell for a group hike at the Laura Hare Nature P
 reserve at Downey Hill\, one of Brown County’s most scenic and biologica
 lly rich forests. This hike will take us along the full 5-mile loop trail 
 as we explore upland ridges\, deep ravines\, and mesic hardwood forests. A
 long the way\, we’ll pause frequently to observe and identify native pla
 nts\, discuss forest ecology\, and share our collective curiosity for the 
 botanical diversity of this rugged landscape. From towering trees to under
 story wildflowers and late-summer surprises\, this will be a leisurely-pac
 ed hike focused on learning and connection with nature.
LOCATION:The Laura Hare Nature Preserve at Downey Hill
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2025/06/group-hike-laura-hare-nature-pre
 serve-at-downey-hill/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
